</span>]]></description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Oct 2025 14:03:39 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Resizeable BAR support on the Raspberry Pi</title><link>https://www.jeffgeerling.com/blog/2025/resizeable-bar-support-on-raspberry-pi</link><description><![CDATA[<span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Resizeable BAR support on the Raspberry Pi</span>

            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><p>While not an <em>absolute</em> requirement for modern graphics card support on Linux, <a href="https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/support/articles/000090831/graphics.html">Resizeable BAR</a> support makes GPUs go faster, by allowing GPUs to throw data back and forth on the PCIe bus in chunks larger than 256 MB.</p>

<p>In January, I opened an issue in the Raspberry Pi Linux repo, <a href="https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux/issues/6621">Resizable BAR support on Pi 5</a>.</p>

<p><img src="https://www.jeffgeerling.com/sites/default/files/images/sparkle-intel-arc-b580-on-raspberry-pi-500-plus.jpg" width="700" height="394" class="insert-image" data-insert-type="image" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="insert-image-f4dc2a6a-8fd9-44f5-8ac8-c557dc843deb" data-insert-attach="{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;f4dc2a6a-8fd9-44f5-8ac8-c557dc843deb&quot;,&quot;attributes&quot;:{&quot;alt&quot;:[&quot;alt&quot;,&quot;description&quot;],&quot;title&quot;:[&quot;title&quot;]}}" alt="Intel Arc B580 on Raspberry Pi 500+"></p></div>
